n communities. These places and the interactions they foster shape reentry outcomes, including re-offending, surveillance, relationship formation, and access to opportunities. This book sheds crucial new light on the processes of reentry and desistance, tying them intimately to space and community, including dynamics around race, gender, gentrification, homelessness, and transportation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aPrisonersxDeinstitutionalizationxSocial aspectszMassachusettszBoston. 0aPrisonersxDeinstitutionalizationzMassachusettszBostony21st centuryvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520976733?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520976733423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520976733/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022  aZDB-23-UCY